ry":"Inez Taylor於1321年出生在英國素可。她與William Scott II結婚。他們至少是1個兒子的父母。她去世於1350年在英國肯特布拉布恩享年29歲。"},"zh-hans":{"1321–1350":"1321年–1350年","1313–1350":"1313年–1350年","1335–1361":"1335年–1361年","1337":"1337年","1335":"1335年","1313":"1313年","1321":"1321年","1453":"1453年","1350":"1350年","1361":"1361年","1328":"1328年","Sussex, England":"英国素可","Brabourne, Kent, England":"英国肯特布拉布恩","lifeSummary":"Inez Taylor于1321年出生在英国素可。她与William Scott II结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。她去世于1350年在英国肯特布拉布恩享年29岁。"},"hr":{"1321–1350":"1321.–1350.","1313–1350":"1313–1350.","1335–1361":"1335.–1361","1337":"1337","1335":"1335.","1313":"1313","1321":"1321.","1453":"1453","1350":"1350.","1361":"1361","1328":"1328","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","Brabourne, Kent, England":"Brabourne, Kent, England"},"cs":{"1321–1350":"1321–1350","1313–1350":"1313–1350","1335–1361":"1335–1361","1337":"1337","1335":"1335","1313":"1313","1321":"1321","1453":"1453","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","1328":"1328","Sussex, England":"Sussex, Anglie","Brabourne, Kent, England":"Brabourne, Kent, Anglie"},"da":{"1321–1350":"1321–1350","1313–1350":"1313–1350","1335–1361":"1335–1361","1337":"1337","1335":"1335","1313":"1313","1321":"1321","1453":"1453","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","1328":"1328","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","Brabourne, Kent, England":"Brabourne, Kent, England"},"nl":{"1321–1350":"1321–1350","1313–1350":"1313–1350","1335–1361":"1335–1361","1337":"1337","1335":"1335","1313":"1313","1321":"1321","1453":"1453","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","1328":"1328","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","Brabourne, Kent, England":"Brabourne, Kent, England"},"en":{"1321–1350":"1321–1350","1313–1350":"1313–1350","1335–1361":"1335–1361","1337":"1337","1335":"1335","1313":"1313","1321":"1321","1453":"1453","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","1328":"1328","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","Brabourne, Kent, England":"Brabourne, Kent, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Taylor","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English, Scottish, and Irish: occupational name for a tailor, from Anglo-Norman French, Middle English <i>taillour</i> ‘tailor’ (Old French <i>tailleor</i>, <i>tailleur</i>; Late Latin <i>taliator</i>, from <i>taliare</i> ‘to cut’). The surname is extremely common in Britain and Ireland. In North America, it has absorbed equivalents from other languages, many of which are also common among Ashkenazic Jews, for example German   Schneider   and Hungarian   Szabo  . It is also very common among African Americans.","In some cases also an Americanized form of French   Terrien   ‘owner of a farmland’ or of its altered forms, such as   Therrien   and   Terrian  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Tayloe","meanings":["Altered form of English, Scottish, and Irish   Taylor  ."]},{"name":"Schneider","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Hans, Otto, Franz, Erwin, Fritz, Dieter, Manfred, Heinz, Alois, Ewald, Helmut.","German and Jewish (Ashkenazic): occupational name for a tailor, literally ‘cutter’, from Middle High German <i>snīder</i>, German <i>Schneider</i>, Yiddish <i>shnayder</i>. The same term was sometimes used to denote a woodcutter. This surname is also established in many other parts of Europe, notably in France (Alsace and Lorraine), the Netherlands, Hungary, Poland, and Czechia. In Czechia, Slovakia, Croatia, and Slovenia it is also established in Slavicized forms (see 2 below). In part, <i>Schneider</i> is a Gottscheerish (i.e. Gottschee German) surname, originating from the Kočevsko region in Lower Carniola, Slovenia (see   Kocevar  ). Compare   Sneider   1,   Snider   1, and   Snyder   1.","Germanized form of Czech, Slovak, Croatian, and Slovenian <b>Šnajdr</b> or <b>Šnajder</b>, and Czech <b>Šneidr</b>, <b>Šneider</b>, <b>Šnejdr</b>, and <b>Šnejder</b>, surnames of German origin (see above)."]},{"name":"Tayler","meanings":["English: variant of   Taylor  ."]},{"name":"Tailor","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Pravin, Dilip, Mahesh, Sanjay, Kanchan, Kaushik, Manilal, Mohanlal, Navnit, Shailesh, Ajay, Alpana.","Indian (Gujarat and Mumbai): mainly Parsi occupational name from the English word <i>tailor</i>.","English: variant of   Taylor  ."]}]},{"name":"Inez","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: Same as Agnes, (kind)."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":7,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705193,"age":16,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Inez Taylor was born in 1321, in Sussex, England. She married William Scott II. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1350, in Brabourne, Kent, England, at the age of 29."},"et":{"1321–1350":"1321–1350","1313–1350":"1313–1350","1335–1361":"1335–1361","1337":"1337","1335":"1335","1313":"1313","1321":"1321","1453":"1453","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","1328":"1328","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","Brabourne, Kent, England":"Brabourne, Kent, England"},"fi":{"1321–1350":"1321–1350","1313–1350":"1313–1350","1335–1361":"1335–1361","1337":"1337","1335":"1335","1313":"1313","1321":"1321","1453":"1453","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","1328":"1328","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","Brabourne, Kent, England":"Brabourne, Kent, England"},"fr":{"1321–1350":"1321–1350","1313–1350":"1313–1350","1335–1361":"1335–1361","1337":"1337","1335":"1335","1313":"1313","1321":"1321","1453":"1453","1350":"1350","1361":"1361","1328":"1328","Sussex, England":"Sussex, Angleterre","Brabourne, Kent, England":"Brabourne, Kent, Angleter